      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CONCRETE STORM (1) was never in the hunt on debut at Canterbury after racing rearwards from a wide alley. Goes from the outside stall to the fence this time so he can travel closer. Watch for a much better performance. POMELO CHAMOMILE (9) raced wide without cover which made her job very difficult first-up over 900m at Newcastle. Will appreciate the extra 200m and from a nice alley is a genuine contender. MOROSINI (8) is a first starter for the Bjorn Baker stable. The latest of her three trials was the most impressive so she seems to be coming along nicely. Market watch on debutant DON'T LOOK BACK (3) who placed in a recent Wyong trial.",
